The name of a fork state cannot be empty.
The name of a join state cannot be empty.

UML:Constraint.name: action needs to be of known type

UML:BooleanExpression.body: context JBpmAction inv: nodeEnter or nodeLeave or task or beforeSignal or afterSignal or timer

UML:Comment.name: This element needs to represent either an 'after signal', 'before signal', 'node enter', 'node leave', 'timer' or 'task'. This is done by attaching the appropriate stereotype to the deferrable event.

UML:BooleanExpression.body: context JBpmPseudostate inv: split implies name->notEmpty()

UML:Comment.name: When you model a fork you must give it a (non-empty) name.

UML:BooleanExpression.body: context JBpmPseudostate inv: decisionPoint implies name->notEmpty()

UML:Comment.name: When you model a decision point you must give it a (non-empty) name.

UML:BooleanExpression.body: context JBpmPseudostate inv: collect implies name->notEmpty()

UML:Comment.name: When you model a join you must give it a (non-empty) name.

UML:Constraint.name: outgoing transitions need guards when exiting a pseudostate

UML:BooleanExpression.body: context JBpmPseudostate inv: decisionPoint implies outgoings->forAll(guard->notEmpty())

UML:Comment.name: Transitions exiting a decision point each need a guard.

UML:Constraint.name: outgoing transitions need names when there is more than one exiting a node

UML:BooleanExpression.body: context JBpmNode inv: outgoings->size() > 1 implies outgoings->forAll(name->notEmpty())

UML:Comment.name: When more than one transition is exiting a node it is required for them all to have a non-empty name.

UML:BooleanExpression.body: context JBpmAction inv: timer implies dueDate->notEmpty()

UML:Comment.name: Timers need to have their due date specified, use the corresponding tagged value to set it.

UML:Constraint.name: timers sometimes require the transition tag

UML:BooleanExpression.body: context JBpmAction inv: let transitionName : String = timerTransition in (timer and state.outgoings->size() > 1) implies (transitionName->notEmpty() and state.outgoings->one(name = transitionName))

UML:Comment.name: If a timer is modeled on a state with two or more outgoing transitions then this timer needs to know which one to take after execution, this is done by means of a tagged value.

UML:Constraint.name: split needs names on all outgoing transitions

UML:BooleanExpression.body: context JBpmPseudostate inv: split implies outgoings->forAll(name|name->notEmpty())

UML:Comment.name: All fork-nodes require their outgoing transitions to have a non-empty name, otherwise jBpm will not be able to distinguish between them when creating child tokens.

UML:Constraint.name: name must not conflict with definition

UML:Comment.name: The name of this node's class will conflict with the name of the interface it is implementing, which is derived from the use-case name. Please either change the name of this node or the name of the encapsulating use-case.
